## Authentication

### Two-Legged OAuth (Client Credentials)

For server-to-server integrations using client credentials:

```go
package main

import (
    "context"
    learn "{{langConfig.module}}"
)

func main() {
    client := learn.NewClient(
        "your-institution.blackboard.com",
        "your-client-id",
        "your-client-secret",
    )
    ctx := context.Background()
    _ = ctx
    _ = client
}
```

### Three-Legged OAuth (Authorization Code + PKCE)

For user-delegated access (e.g., acting on behalf of a student or instructor):

```go
auth := learn.NewOAuth2Client(
    "https://your-institution.blackboard.com",
    "your-client-id",
    "your-client-secret",
    "{{auth.twoLegged.tokenEndpoint}}",
)

// Step 1: Generate the authorization URL with PKCE
result, err := auth.GetAuthorizationURL("https://your-app.com/callback", "read", "csrf-tok")
if err != nil {
    log.Fatal(err)
}
// Redirect the user to result.URL
// Store result.CodeVerifier

// Step 2: After the user authorizes, exchange the code
err = auth.ExchangeCode(ctx, codeFromCallback, "https://your-app.com/callback", result.CodeVerifier)
if err != nil {
    log.Fatal(err)
}

// The auth client now holds the user's access token
token, _ := auth.GetToken(ctx)
```

## Quick Start

```go
// List courses
courses, err := client.Courses().List(ctx)
if err != nil {
    log.Fatal(err)
}
fmt.Println(courses)

// Get a single course
course, err := client.Courses().Get(ctx, "externalId:INTRO-101")
if err != nil {
    log.Fatal(err)
}
fmt.Println(course.Name)
```

## Error Handling

```go
import learn "{{langConfig.module}}"

course, err := client.Courses().Get(ctx, "_invalid_id_")
if err != nil {
    var apiErr *learn.APIError
    if errors.As(err, &apiErr) {
        if apiErr.IsNotFoundError() {
            fmt.Println("Course not found")
        } else if apiErr.IsRateLimitError() {
            fmt.Printf("Rate limited — retry after %s\n", apiErr.RetryAfter)
        } else {
            fmt.Printf("API error %d: %s\n", apiErr.StatusCode, apiErr.Message)
        }
    }
}
```

## Pagination

Paginated methods return Go 1.23+ iterators:

```go
for course, err := range client.Courses().ListAll(ctx) {
    if err != nil {
        log.Fatal(err)
    }
    fmt.Println(course.Name)
}
```

